space%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ERussia's%20top%20court%20declares%20the%20'international%20LGBT%20public%20movement'%20an%20extremist%20organization%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20repression.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20approves%20the%20ban%20application%20by%20the%20Justice%20Ministry%20in%20a%20closed%20hearing.%20Activists%20express%20alarm%20as%20the%20law%20could%20be%20used%20to%20threaten%20any%20LGBT%20person%20with%20long%20jail%20sentences.%20The%20ruling%20also%20makes%20it%20possible%20to%20ban%20any%20LGBT%20symbols.%20The%20Kremlin%20is%20placing%20increasing%20emphasis%20on%20%E2%80%9Ctraditional%20values%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-bans-lgbt-movement-stirring-fears-of-new-crackdown%2Farticleshow%2F105632873.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-bans-lgbt-movement-stirring-fears-of-new-crackdown%2Famp_articleshow%2F105632873.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-bans-lgbt-movement-stirring-fears-of-new-crackdown%2Famp_articleshow%2F105632873.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Haritha%20Haaram%3A%20How%20Telangana's%20Afforestation%20Project%20Proved%20Detrimental%20to%20Adivasi%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30195518%2FEffect-6.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20electioneering%20in%20Telangana%2C%20several%20issues%20of%20welfare%2C%20development%2C%20and%20various%20demographic%20groups%20came%20to%20the%20fore.%20However%2C%20Haritha%20Haaram%2C%20a%20pet%20project%20of%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20government%2C%20did%20not%20garner%20much%20attention.%20The%20stated%20objective%20of%20the%20initiative%20is%20to%20promote%20afforestation%20across%20the%20state.%20The%20initiative%20helps%20us%20understand%20the%20intersection%20of%20environmental%20politics%2C%20marginalisation%20of%20Adivasis%2C%20and%20the%20continued%20reliance%20on%20outdated%2C%20unscientific%2C%20and%20colonial%20conservation%20practices%20followed%20by%20the%20forest%20bureaucracy%20in%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaritha%20Haaram%3A%20Boon%20or%20bane%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaritha%20Haaram%2C%20which%20was%20rolled%20out%20in%202014%2C%20is%20a%20state-wide%20plantation%20programme%20for%20planting%20seedlings%20to%20increase%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20forest%20cover%20to%2033%25%20from%2024%25.%20With%20a%20massive%20investment%20of%20Rs%208%2C511%20crore%2C%20as%20per%20December%202022%20estimates%2C%20the%20BRS%20government%20claims%20to%20have%20planted%20around%20266%20crore%20saplings%2C%20surpassing%20the%20target%20of%20230%20crore%20saplings%20originally%20envisioned%20as%20part%20of%20the%20programme.%20It%20is%2C%20however%2C%20unclear%20how%20many%20of%20these%20saplings%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fharitha-haram-266-cr-saplings-planted-8-yrs-telangana-how-many-survived-170925%5C%22%3Esurvived%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMultiple%20afforestation%20efforts%20have%20been%20on%20inside%20the%20forested%20areas%20and%20in%20non-forested%20areas%2C%20which%20include%20grasslands%2C%20wasteland%2C%20and%20community%20commons.%20According%20to%20officials%2C%2090%25%20of%20the%20seedlings%20survived%20inside%20the%20forested%20zones%2C%20whereas%20the%20success%20rate%20is%2070%25-80%25%20for%20the%20plantations%20outside%20of%20forested%20areas.%20This%20is%20not%20verified%20by%20any%20independent%20auditor%20or%20scientific%20study%2C%20yet%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20has%20endorsed%20and%20encouraged%20Haritha%20Haaram%20after%20eight%20years%20of%20its%20supposed%20%E2%80%98success%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Telangana%20is%20among%20the%20top%20states%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelanganatoday.com%2Fover-3-lakh-hectares-of-forest-land-diverted-under-forest-conservation-act-in-15-years-govt%5C%22%3Edivert%20forest%20lands%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20non-forestry%20activities.%20According%20to%20the%20data%20from%20the%20Union%20Environment%20Ministry%2C%20Telangana%20diverted%2019%2C419%20hectares%20of%20forest%20land%20over%20the%20last%2015%20years%20under%20the%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Act%2C%201980.%20Here%20is%20the%20contradiction%2C%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20rapidly%20depleting%20natural%20forests%20for%20non-forestry%20purposes%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%2C%20parallel%20afforestation%20programmes%20underway%2C%20which%20are%20aligned%20with%20the%20Compensatory%20Afforestation%20Fund%20Management%20Authority%20(CAMPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fbioscience%2Farticle%2F70%2F11%2F947%2F5903754%3Flogin%3Dtrue%26s%3D09%5C%22%3EVarious%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ecologyandsociety.org%2Fvol25%2Fiss4%2Fart1%2F%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.researchsquare.com%2Ffiles%2Frs-289460%2Fv1_covered.pdf%3Fc%3D1637595601%5C%22%3Edemonstrated%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0305750X22000547%5C%22%3Eproblems%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20such%20contradictory%20policies.%20Increasingly%2C%20studies%20in%20India%20and%20elsewhere%20have%20argued%20about%20the%20limitations%20of%20afforestation%20in%20certain%20landscapes.%20Replacing%20natural%20forests%20is%20not%20the%20one-size-fits-all%20solution%20for%20climate%20change%20mitigation%20strategy%2C%20for%20it%20harms%20local%20ecology%2C%20and%20dispossesses%20pastoral%20and%20indigenous%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20article%20will%20not%20dwell%20on%20the%20scientific%20unviability%20of%20these%20programmes%2C%20nor%20the%20claims%20of%20Haritha%20Haaram%20being%20%E2%80%98successful%E2%80%99.%20It%20is%20concerned%20with%20the%20plight%20of%20small-scale%20farmers%20and%20Adivasis%20who%20have%20been%20displaced%20due%20to%20the%20plantation%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EForest%20Rights%20Act%2C%202006%20and%20Settlement%20of%20Rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Forest%20Right%20Act%202006%20is%20a%20landmark%20legislation%20enacted%20to%20correct%20historical%20injustices%20meted%20upon%20the%20Adivasi%2C%20forest-dwelling%2C%20and%20pastoral%20communities%20during%20the%20colonial%20period%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20post-independent%20era.%20The%20Preamble%20of%20the%20Act%20states%20that%20historical%20injustices%20must%20be%20addressed.%20The%20Act%20ensures%20recognition%20of%20community%20rights%20and%20livelihood%20security%20for%20the%20Adivasis%20or%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(ST)%20and%20Other%20Forest-Dwelling%20(OTFD)%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F10143411%2FInto-the-forest-scenery-Gorumara-forest-India-86509-pixahive-1024x631-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F10143411%2FInto-the-forest-scenery-Gorumara-forest-India-86509-pixahive-1024x631-1.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F10143411%2FInto-the-forest-scenery-Gorumara-forest-India-86509-pixahive-1024x631-1-300x185.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-606748%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22631%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Roy%2FPixahive%2C%20CC0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdivasis%20consist%20of%209.3%25%20of%20the%20total%20population%20in%20Telangana%20(Census%202011).%20Some%20of%20the%20major%20tribal%20communities%20in%20Telangana%20include%20the%20Lambada%2C%20Gond%2C%20Kolam%2C%20Thoti%2C%20Pardhan%2C%20Mannewar%2C%20Nayakpod%2C%20Koya%2C%20Kondareddy%2C%20Chenchu%2C%20Nakkala%2C%20Yerukala%2C%20Yanadi%2C%20among%20others.%20Pastoral%20communities%20like%20Kurumbas%20and%20Gola%20Kurumbs%20are%20also%20part%20of%20the%20ST%20communities.%20Most%20of%20the%20forest%20areas%20of%20Telangana%20are%20located%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20undivided%20districts%20of%20Khammam%2C%20Warangal%2C%20Adilabad%2C%20and%20Mahabubnagar.%20The%20total%20forest%20area%20in%20Telangana%20is%20around%2063.50%20lakh%20acres%20(26%2C904%20sq.%20km).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanchronicle.com%2Fnation%2Fcurrent-affairs%2F010719%2Ftrs-activists-beat-up-woman-forest-officers-staff-with-sticks-poles.html%5C%22%3Emultiple%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2FTelangana-Tribals-Resist-Haritha-Haram-Podu-Lands%5C%22%3Emedia%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fwhy-telangana-is-seeing-an-increase-in-violent-clashes-between-tribals-forest-officials%2F731548%2F%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20shown%20the%20violent%20side%20of%20the%20Haritha%20Haaram%20programme%2C%20which%20involves%20the%20plantation%20of%20saplings%20as%20well%20as%20the%20large-scale%20digging%20of%20trenches%20around%20Adivasi%20habitations.%20This%20implies%20the%20denial%20of%20access%20to%20forest%20lands%20for%20those%20who%20are%20dependent%20on%20the%20same%20for%20farming%20or%20grazing%20purposes%2C%20conflicting%20with%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20FRA.%20The%20provisions%20of%20FRA%20clearly%20state%20that%20eviction%20of%20forest%20dwellers%20without%20settlement%20of%20rights%20is%20a%20violation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Ftelangana-forest-officer-killing-podu-cultivation%5C%22%3ETelangana%3A%20Forest%20Officer%E2%80%99s%20Killing%20Brings%20to%20Fore%20Issue%20of%20Podu%20Cultivation%20Again%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20districts%20of%20Bhadradri%20Kothagudem%2C%20Mancherial%2C%20Warangal%2C%20Adilabad%2C%20and%20Asifabad%2C%20the%20forest%20department%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fpodu-land-controversy-telangana-adivasis-call-bandh-july-11-165671%5C%22%3Eforcibly%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2FTussle-Between-Farmers-Forest-Officials-Telangana%5C%22%3Eevicting%3C%2Fa%3E%20tribal%20households%20engaged%20in%20%3Cem%3Epodu%3C%2Fem%3E%20cultivation%20(a%20traditional%20form%20of%20shifting%20cultivation)%20on%20forest%20lands.%20The%20department%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fharassment-over-podu-land-issue-adivasi-advocates-demand-national-intervention-165768%5C%22%3Ebooking%20false%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20cases%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20in%20several%20villages%20because%20those%20tribals%20do%20not%20possess%20Recognition%20of%20Forest%20Rights%20pattas%20for%20those%20lands.%20While%20the%20plantation%20drive%20using%20Compensatory%20Afforestation%20Fund%20Management%20Authority%20(CAMPA)%20and%20other%20funds%20dilutes%20the%20key%20provisions%20of%20the%20FRA%20and%20Panchayat%20Extension%20to%20Scheduled%20Areas%20Act%20(PESA%20Act)%2C%20it%20also%20comes%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20denudation%20of%20natural%2C%20biodiverse%20forests%2C%20and%20its%20replacement%20with%20monoculture%20plantations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabitat%20rights%20of%20the%20Particularly%20Vulnerable%20Tribal%20Groups%20(PVTGs)%20have%20also%20not%20been%20recognised%20under%20the%20FRA%20in%20Telangana.%20Under%20the%20amended%20FRA%20Rules%2C%202012%2C%20the%20District%20Level%20Committee%20(DLC)%20chaired%20by%20the%20district%20collector%2C%20is%20mandated%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20habitat%20rights%20of%20PVTGs%20are%20recognised.%20Such%20PVTG%20communities%20have%20also%20been%20facing%20the%20threat%20of%20eviction%20from%20their%20habitats%20for%20Tiger%20Reserve%20projects%20in%20Kawal%20and%20Amrabad%20Tiger%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20hardly%20any%20records%20or%20reports%20of%20recognition%20of%20Community%20Rights%20(CR%2FCFR)%20and%20Habitat%20Rights%20for%20PVTG%20communities%20and%20other%20ST%20communities%20in%20National%20Parks%20and%20Protected%20Areas.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20lack%20of%20communication%20on%20rejected%20FRA%20claims%20and%20why%20fresh%20claims%20have%20not%20been%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20inconvenient%20flashback%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30194017%2FTelangana-FRA-Implementation-2018-2023.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30194017%2FTelangana-FRA-Implementation-2018-2023.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30194017%2FTelangana-FRA-Implementation-2018-2023-300x116.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30194017%2FTelangana-FRA-Implementation-2018-2023-1024x394.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687147%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESource%3A%C2%A0%20Ministry%20of%20Tribal%20Affairs.%20Monthly%20Progress%20Report%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftribal.nic.in%2FFRA.aspx%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ftribal.nic.in%2FFRA.aspx%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3E(June%202023)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20above%20table%20shows%20the%20progress%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%20in%20FRA%20implementation%20in%20Telangana%2C%20which%20can%20be%20summed%20up%20as%20dismal%20and%20negligent.%20Of%20the%2020%2C305%20odd%20claims%20under%20the%20category%20of%20individual%20forest%20rights%20(IFR)%20and%20community%20forest%20rights%20(CFR)%20since%20March%202018%2C%20only%203%2C176%20titles%20have%20been%20approved%2C%20which%20is%20only%2015%25%20of%20the%20claims.%20As%20many%20as%2010%2C669%20or%2051%25%20of%20claims%20have%20been%20rejected.%20There%20were%202%2C808%20community%20rights%20title%20claims%20filed%20as%20of%20June%202023%2C%20and%20only%20102%20were%20recognised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20worrying%20is%20that%20as%20of%20June%202023%2C%20overall%2092.7%25%20of%20the%20claims%20were%20disposed%20of%20with%20respect%20to%20claims%20received%2C%20whereas%20only%2047%25%20of%20the%20total%20claims%20were%20approved.%20As%20many%20as%2094%2C426%20claims%20were%20rejected%2C%20and%20little%20has%20been%20done%20so%20far%20to%20convey%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20rejections%20of%20claims%20to%20the%20claimants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fharassment-over-podu-land-issue-adivasi-advocates-demand-national-intervention-165768%5C%22%3EReports%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20suggested%20that%20rejection%20is%20often%20based%20on%20frivolous%20grounds%2C%20completely%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20FRA%2C%202006%2C%20which%20clearly%20states%20that%20detailed%20reasons%20must%20be%20provided%20for%20rejection%20of%20claims.%20Based%20on%20the%20data%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frightsandresources.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F11%2FIndia-Promise-and-Performance-National-Report_CFRLA_2016.pdf%5C%22%3ECFR%20%E2%80%93%20LA%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%202016%20on%20the%20potential%20of%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%20%26amp%3B%20Community%20Forest%20Rights%20in%20India%2C%20it%20was%20found%20that%20Telangana%20has%20almost%2040%20lakh%20acres%20of%20forest%20land%20which%20has%20the%20potential%20for%20recognition%20under%20the%20FRA%2C%202006%20of%20various%20communities%2C%20including%20both%20ST%20and%20OTFD.%20More%20than%2010%20million%20people%2C%20which%20includes%20STs%2C%20pastoralist%20communities%2C%20and%20OTFDs%20may%20benefit%20from%20the%20provisions%20of%20FRA%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20framing%20PESA%20rules%20in%202011%20and%20adopted%20after%20reorganisation%20of%20the%20separate%20state%20in%202014%2C%20there%20has%20practically%20been%20no%20implementation%20of%20PESA%20provisions%20in%20Telangana.%20The%20failure%20to%20constitute%20habitation-level%20Gram%20Sabhas%2C%20and%20strengthen%20the%20same%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20poor%20implementation%20of%20FRA%20across%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20primacy%20of%20Gram%20Sabha%20consent%20is%20being%20completely%20bypassed%20in%20the%20formulation%20or%20implementation%20of%20key%20decisions%20related%20to%20land%20acquisition%20for%20public%20purpose%20projects%2C%20use%20of%20Compensatory%20Afforestation%20Fund%20Management%20Authority%20(CAMPA)%20funds%20for%20afforestation%20schemes%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20Harita%20Haaram%20or%20even%20selection%20of%20beneficiaries%20for%20housing%20schemes%20under%20the%20recently%20announced%20Gruha%20Lakshmi%20scheme%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfforestation%20with%20FRA%2C%202006%20%E2%80%93%20The%20way%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20afforestation%20schemes%20by%20the%20Telangana%20government%2C%20despite%20their%20perceived%20%E2%80%98success%E2%80%99%2C%20find%20little%20or%20no%20place%20in%20the%20electoral%20discourse%20of%20the%20ruling%20party.%20After%20all%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20recognise%20that%20politics%20is%20not%20always%20about%20what%20is%20being%20said%2C%20but%20it%20is%20often%20about%20what%20is%20not%20being%20said.%20Many%20Adivasi%20families%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Ftelangana-govt-stalls-podu-land-scrutiny-nearly-one-lakh-adivasis-hit-162756%5C%22%3Edisplaced%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20those%20who%20have%20resisted%20face%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20before%20the%20elections%2C%20chief%20minister%20K.%20Chandrashekar%20Rao%20said%20that%20some%20cases%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Fpodu-govt-to-withdraw-cases-against-tribals%2Farticleshow%2F101406314.cms%5C%22%3Ewithdrawn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20the%20indignity%20that%20ensued%20in%20the%20process%20might%20have%20damaged%20the%20ruling%20party%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20prospects%20among%20Adivasis%20and%20marginal%20cultivators%20in%20predominantly%20Adivasi%20districts%20and%20constituencies.%20That%20is%20perhaps%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20ruling%20party%E2%80%99s%20silence%20on%20its%20flagship%20afforestation%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20afforestation%20programme%20has%20extraordinary%20ambitions.%20However%2C%20the%20programme%20can%20only%20be%20successful%20by%20including%20and%20consulting%20various%20communities.%20Existing%20laws%20like%20PESA%20and%20FRA%20offer%20relevant%20solutions%20to%20prevent%20governments%20from%20falling%20into%20the%20trap%20of%20an%20exclusionary%20model%20of%20conservation%2C%20which%20undermines%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20Adivasis%20and%20other%20forest-dependent%20communities.%20Recognition%20of%20forest%20rights%20%E2%80%93%20both%20individual%20and%20community%20%E2%80%93%20is%20central%20to%20the%20integrity%20of%20our%20ecological%20and%20social%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnvironmental%20concerns%20cannot%20isolate%20the%20issues%20of%20the%20Adivasis%20and%20the%20recognition%20of%20forest-dependent%20communities.%20The%20electoral%20value%20of%20these%20issues%20cannot%20be%20undermined%2C%20and%20political%20parties%20must%20speak%20up%20on%20these%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E*619%20Community%20Rights%20titles%20were%20cancelled%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20violating%20the%20FRA.%20These%20Community%20Forest%20Rights%20(CFR)%20titles%20have%20been%20granted%20to%20the%20Vana%20Samrakshana%20Samitis%20(VSS)%20which%20are%20under%20the%20control%20of%20the%20forest%20department%20and%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20not%20covered%20under%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98forest%20dwelling%20Scheduled%20tribes%20and%20other%20traditional%20forest%20dwellers%E2%80%9D%20as%20given%20in%20Sections%202(c)%20and%202(o)%20of%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%20and%20therefore%20these%20committees%20cannot%20be%20considered%20as%20claimants%20for%20granting%20community%20forest%20Rights.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E**102%20titles%20are%20still%20recognised%20as%20Community%20Rights%2FCFR%20titles%3B%20however%2C%20the%20details%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20these%20rights%20remain%20elusive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnAzam%20Danish%20is%20an%20independent%20researcher.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701356440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30195518%2FEffect-6.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fharitha-haaram-how-telanganas-afforestation-project-proved-detrimental-to-adivasi-rights%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20the%20flip%20side%20of%20the%20positive%20perception%20it%20garners%2C%20the%20BRS%20government's%20afforestation%20programme%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20denying%20access%20to%20forest%20lands%20for%20those%20who%20are%20dependent%20on%20them%20for%20farming%20or%20grazing%20purposes%2C%20conflicting%20with%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fharitha-haaram-how-telanganas-afforestation-project-proved-detrimental-to-adivasi-rights%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%