2C%20thanks%20in%20large%20part%20to%20the%20cunning%20and%20determination%20of%20my%20mother.%20In%20both%20a%20professional%20and%20personal%20sense%2C%20I%20am%20aware%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheintercept.com%2F2023%2F05%2F23%2Fhenry-kissinger-cambodia-bombing-survivors%2F%5C%22%3Enear%2050-year%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E%20Kissinger%E2%80%99s%20policies%20during%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20have%20had%20on%20the%20country%20of%20my%20birth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20the%20murderous%20regime%20that%20forced%20my%20family%20to%20leave%20was%2C%20in%20part%2C%20encouraged%20by%20Kissinger%E2%80%99s%20policies.%20The%20cluster%20bombs%20dropped%20on%20Cambodia%20under%20Kissinger%E2%80%99s%20watch%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.the-monitor.org%2Fen-gb%2Freports%2F2023%2Fcambodia%2Fimpact.aspx%5C%22%3Econtinue%20to%20destroy%20the%20lives%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20any%20man%2C%20woman%2C%20or%20child%20who%20happens%20across%20them.%20Indeed%2C%20when%20the%20current%20U.S.%20administration%20announced%20its%20intention%20in%202023%20to%20provide%20cluster%20bombs%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20Cambodia%20was%20quick%20to%20call%20out%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fasia%2Fsoutheast-asia%2Farticle%2F3227129%2Fukraine-should-shun-us-cluster-bombs-learn-cambodias-painful-experience-pm-hun-sen%5C%22%3Elingering%20damage%20the%20munition%20causes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Island%20of%20peace%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECounterfactuals%20are%20not%20the%20best%20tool%20for%20the%20historian%3B%20no%20one%20can%20say%20how%20Cambodia%20would%20have%20developed%20were%20it%20not%20for%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20and%20US%20intervention%20in%20Southeast%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20prior%20to%20the%20US%20bombing%20of%20Cambodia%2C%20the%20country%20was%20touted%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1997%2F09%2F01%2Fworld%2Fin-cambodia-king-sihanouk-once-more-moves-deftly-among-powers.html%5C%22%3EIsland%20of%20Peace%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20by%20then-leader%20Prince%20Norodom%20Sihanouk%2C%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-1991-11-08-me-813-story.html%5C%22%3Edeveloping%20economy%20and%20relative%20stability%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Cambodia%20gained%20independence%20from%20its%20French%20colonial%20masters%20in%201953%2C%20Sihanouk%20presided%20over%20what%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fbooks%2Fabs%2Fviolence-and-the-civilising-process-in-cambodia%2Fgolden-years-of-sihanoukism-19551966%2F14A4A3B5B9AF2C9846BCDF518302B5D8%5C%22%3Eseen%20as%20a%20golden%20age%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Cambodia.%20Even%20Lee%20Kuan%20Yew%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20modern-day%20Singapore%2C%20visited%20Cambodia%20to%20learn%20lessons%20on%20nation-building.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%E2%80%99s%20independence%20from%20France%20did%20not%20require%20any%20hard%20fight.%20Neighbouring%20Vietnam%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20gained%20independence%20only%20after%20the%20bitter%20anti-colonial%20First%20Indochina%20War%2C%20which%20concluded%20with%20a%20rout%20of%20French%20troops%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.state.gov%2Fmilestones%2F1953-1960%2Fdien-bien-phu%5C%22%3Eat%20%C4%90i%E1%BB%87n%20Bi%C3%AAn%20Ph%E1%BB%A7%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201954.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Cambodia%E2%80%99s%20location%20drew%20it%20into%20the%20subsequent%20war%20between%20the%20newly%20independent%20communist%20North%20Vietnam%20and%20the%20US-backed%20South%20Vietnam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECambodia%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20officially%20a%20party%20in%20the%20Vietnam%20War%2C%20with%20Sihanouk%20declaring%20the%20country%20neutral.%20But%20Washington%20looked%20for%20ways%20to%20disrupt%20communist%20North%20Vietnamese%20operations%20along%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nga.mil%2Fdefining-moments%2FHo_Chi_Minh_Trail.html%5C%22%3EHo%20Chi%20Minh%20Trail%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20cut%20across%20Cambodia%E2%80%99s%20east%2C%20with%20Sihanouk%E2%80%99s%20blessing%2C%20and%20allowed%20the%20resupply%20of%20North%20Vietnamese%20troops%20on%20Cambodian%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKissinger%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98menu%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKissinger%20was%20the%20chief%20architect%20of%20the%20plan%20to%20disrupt%20that%20supply%20line%2C%20and%20what%20he%20came%20up%20with%20was%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vietnamwar50th.com%2F1969-1971_vietnamization%2FOperation-MENU-Begins%2F%5C%22%3EOperation%20Menu%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%20The%20secret%20carpet-bombing%20campaign%20%E2%80%93%20with%20breakfast%2C%20lunch%2C%20dinner%2C%20snack%2C%20dessert%2C%20and%20supper%20representing%20different%20targets%20and%20missions%20within%20Cambodia%20%E2%80%93%20was%20confirmed%20at%20a%20meeting%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%20on%20March%2017%2C%201969.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nixonlibrary.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fvirtuallibrary%2Fdocuments%2Fhaldeman-diaries%2F37-hrhd-journal-vol01-19690317.pdf%5C%22%3Ediary%20entry%20of%20Richard%20Nixon%E2%80%99s%20chief%20of%20staff%2C%20H.%20R.%20Haldeman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reads%3A%20%E2%80%9C%20%E2%80%A6%20Historic%20day.%20K%5Bissinger%5D%E2%80%98s%20%E2%80%98Operation%20Breakfast%E2%80%99%20finally%20came%20off%20at%202%3A00%20pm%20our%20time.%20K%20really%20excited%2C%20as%20is%20P%5Bresident%5D.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30154233%2F52830590697_b316c750b7_o.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30154233%2F52830590697_b316c750b7_o.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30154233%2F52830590697_b316c750b7_o-300x227.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30154233%2F52830590697_b316c750b7_o-1024x774.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687106%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22907%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPresidential%20adviser%20Henry%20Kissinger%2C%20right%2C%20talks%20with%20members%20of%20the%20North%20Vietnam%20delegation%20after%20initialing%20of%20the%20Vietnam%20peace%20agreement%20was%20signed%20in%20Paris%20on%20Jan.%2024%2C%201973.%20From%20left%20are%20Nguyen%20Co%20Thach%2C%20Vice%20Minister%20for%20Foreign%20Affairs%3B%20Xuan%20Thuy%2C%20chief%20of%20the%20delegation%20to%20the%20Paris%20talks%3B%20Nguyen%20Dinh%20Phuong%2C%20interpreter%3B%20Le%20Duc%20Tho%2C%20special%20adviser%20to%20the%20delegation%20in%20Paris%3B%20and%20Kissinger.%20Photo%3A%20flickr.com%2Fmanhhai%2FCC%20BY%202.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nixonlibrary.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fvirtuallibrary%2Fdocuments%2Fhaldeman-diaries%2F37-hrhd-journal-vol01-19690318.pdf%5C%22%3Efollowing%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Haldeman%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CK%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Operation%20Breakfast%E2%80%99%20a%20great%20success.%20He%20came%20beaming%20in%20with%20the%20report%2C%20very%20productive.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%20began%20four%20years%20of%20Kissinger%E2%80%99s%20legally%20dubious%20campaign%20in%20Cambodia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20Kissinger%2C%20Cambodia%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Csideshow%2C%E2%80%9D%20to%20use%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frowman.com%2FISBN%2F9780815412243%2FSideshow-Kissinger-Nixon-and-the-Destruction-of-Cambodia-Revised-Edition%5C%22%3Etitle%20of%20William%20Shawcross%E2%80%99%20damning%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%20exposing%20the%20story%20of%20America%E2%80%99s%20secret%20war%20with%20Cambodia%20from%201969%20to%201973.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20period%2C%20the%20US%20bombing%20of%20neutral%20Cambodia%20saw%20an%20estimated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgsp.yale.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fwalrus_cambodiabombing_oct06.pdf%5C%22%3E2%2C756%2C941%20tons%20of%20ordnance%20dropped%20on%20113%2C716%20targets%20in%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecret%20and%20illegal%20war%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKissinger%20and%20others%20in%20the%20White%20House%20tried%20to%20keep%20the%20campaign%20from%20the%20public%20for%20as%20long%20as%20they%20could%2C%20for%20good%20reason.%20It%20came%20as%20public%20opinion%20in%20the%20US%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2F2009%2F11%2F23%2Fpolling-wars-hawks-vs-doves%2F%5C%22%3Eturning%20against%20American%20involvement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20bombing%20campaign%20is%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frowman.com%2FISBN%2F9780815412243%2FSideshow-Kissinger-Nixon-and-the-Destruction-of-Cambodia-Revised-Edition%5C%22%3Econsidered%20illegal%20under%20international%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20many%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20to%20Kissinger%2C%20the%20ends%20%E2%80%93%20containing%20communism%20%E2%80%93%20seemingly%20justified%20the%20means%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20cost.%20And%20the%20cost%20to%20Cambodians%20was%20huge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20resulted%20in%20the%20direct%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgsp.yale.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fwalrus_cambodiabombing_oct06.pdf%5C%22%3Edeaths%20of%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20Cambodians%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20the%20US%20government%20keeping%20the%20bombings%20secret%20at%20the%20time%2C%20comprehensive%20data%20and%20documentation%20are%20limited.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.irrawaddy.com%2Farticle.php%3Fart_id%3D2412%5C%22%3Eestimates%20on%20the%20number%20of%20deaths%3C%2Fa%3E%20range%20from%20as%20few%20as%2024%2C000%20to%20as%20many%20as%20a%20million.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Ffrontlineworld%2Fstories%2Fcambodia%2Ftl02.html%5C%22%3EMost%20estimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.irrawaddy.com%2Farticle.php%3Fart_id%3D2412%5C%22%3Eput%20the%20death%20toll%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsites.tufts.edu%2Fatrocityendings%2F2015%2F08%2F07%2Fcambodia-u-s-bombing-civil-war-khmer-rouge%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKissinger%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20also%20destabilised%20Cambodia%2C%20leaving%20it%20vulnerable%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcla.umn.edu%2Fchgs%2Fholocaust-genocide-education%2Fresource-guides%2Fcambodia%5C%22%3Ethe%20horrors%20to%20come%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20capital%2C%20Phnom%20Penh%2C%20ballooned%20in%20population%20because%20of%20the%20displacement%20of%20more%20than%20a%20million%20rural%20citizens%20fleeing%20U.S.%20bombs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20bombing%20of%20Cambodian%20citizens%20contributed%20to%20an%20erosion%20of%20trust%20in%20Camodia%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20and%20put%20into%20question%20Sihanouk%E2%80%99s%20policy%20of%20allowing%20the%20North%20Vietnamese%20access%20through%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20east.%20On%20March%2018%2C%201970%2C%20Sihanouk%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2020%2F03%2Fremembering-cambodias-1970-coup%2F%5C%22%3Eousted%20in%20a%20coup%20d%E2%80%99etat%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20replaced%20by%20the%20US-friendly%20Lon%20Nol.%20Direct%20US%20involvement%20in%20the%20coup%20has%20never%20been%20proven%2C%20but%20certainly%2C%20opponents%20to%20Lon%20Nol%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fmywarwithcia00noro%5C%22%3Esaw%20the%20hand%20of%20the%20CIA%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ousted%20Sihanouk%20called%20on%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20rural%20masses%20to%20support%20his%20coalition%20government%20in%20exile%2C%20which%20included%20the%20Khmer%20Rouge.%20Until%20then%2C%20the%20Khmer%20Rouge%20had%20been%20a%20ragtag%20army%20with%20only%20revolutionary%20fantasies.%20But%20with%20Sihanouk%E2%80%99s%20backing%2C%20they%20grew.%20As%20journalist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fnews%2Fnews-desk%2Fthe-fantasy-of-king-sihanouk%5C%22%3EPhilip%20Gourevitch%20noted%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CHis%20name%20became%20the%20Khmer%20Rouge%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20recruitment%20tool.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Kissinger%E2%80%99s%20bombs%20also%20served%20as%20a%20recruitment%20tool.%20The%20Khmer%20Rouge%20was%20able%20to%20capitalise%20on%20the%20anger%20and%20resentment%20of%20Cambodians%20in%20the%20areas%20being%20shelled.%20Rebel%20leaders%20portrayed%20themselves%20as%20a%20force%20to%20protect%20Cambodia%20from%20foreign%20aggression%20and%20restore%20order%20and%20justice%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20ruling%20government%E2%80%99s%20massive%20corruption%20and%20pro-American%20leanings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKissinger%E2%80%99s%20bombing%20campaign%20was%20certainly%20not%20the%20only%20reason%20for%20the%20Khmer%20Rouge%E2%80%99s%20rise%2C%20but%20it%20contributed%20to%20the%20overall%20destabilisation%20of%20Cambodia%20and%20a%20political%20vacuum%20that%20the%20Khmer%20Rouge%20was%20able%20to%20exploit%20and%20eventually%20seize%20power%20%E2%80%93%20which%20it%20did%20in%201975%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsfi.usc.edu%2Fcollections%2Fcambodian-genocide%5C%22%3Eoverthrowing%20the%20government%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELed%20by%20Pol%20Pot%2C%20the%20Khmer%20Rouge%20inflicted%20unimaginable%20atrocities%20upon%20the%20Cambodian%20people.%20Its%20genocidal%20campaign%20against%20political%20opponents%2C%20Cambodian%20minorities%2C%20and%20those%20deemed%20counterrevolutionaries%20saw%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsfi.usc.edu%2Fcollections%2Fcambodian-genocide%5C%22%3Ebetween%201.6%20and%203%20million%20people%20killed%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20executions%2C%20forced%20labor%20and%20starvation%20%E2%80%93%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20then%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scars%20from%20that%20period%20are%20still%20felt%20in%20Cambodia%20today.%20Recent%20research%20even%20points%20to%20the%20economic%20impact%20Kissinger%E2%80%99s%20bombs%20continue%20to%20have%20on%20farmers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fgraphic-detail%2F2021%2F03%2F20%2Famerican-bombing-50-years-ago-still-shapes-cambodian-agriculture%5C%22%3Ewho%20avoid%20richer%2C%20darker%20soil%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20fears%20that%20it%20hides%20unexploded%20ordnance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnti-Americanism%20is%20no%20longer%20prevalent%20at%20the%20everyday%20level%20in%20Cambodia%3B%20indeed%2C%20the%20opposite%20is%20increasingly%20becoming%20true%20as%20China%E2%80%99s%20financial%20and%20political%20embrace%20becomes%20suffocating.%20However%2C%20anti-Americanism%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2Fasia_pacific%2Fthe-former-khmer-rouge-commander-who-still-leads-cambodia-is-again-stoking-anti-american-sentiment%2F2018%2F05%2F11%2F679ea9c8-4cf6-11e8-b966-bfb0da2dad62_story.html%5C%22%3Efrequently%20used%20in%20rhetoric%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20leading%20politicians%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20don%E2%80%99t%20agree%20with%20some%20other%20scholars%20that%20Kissinger%E2%80%99s%20bombing%20campaign%20can%20be%20definitively%20proven%20to%20have%20resulted%20in%20Khmer%20Rouge%20rule.%20But%20in%20my%20view%2C%20it%20no%20doubt%20contributed.%20Hun%20Sen%2C%20Cambodia%E2%80%99s%20autocratic%20leader%20who%20ruled%20for%2038%20years%20before%20passing%20the%20prime%20minister%20baton%20to%20his%20son%20in%20August%202023%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.culturalsurvival.org%2Fpublications%2Fcultural-survival-quarterly%2Ftalk-prime-minister-hun-sen%5C%22%3Ecited%20the%20US%20bombing%20of%20his%20birthplace%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20reason%20he%20joined%20the%20Khmer%20Rouge.%20Many%20others%20joined%20for%20similar%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20such%2C%20the%20devastating%20impact%20of%20Kissinger%E2%80%99s%20policies%20in%20Cambodia%20cannot%20be%20overstated%20%E2%80%93%20they%20contributed%20to%20the%20unraveling%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20social%20fabric%20and%20the%20suffering%20of%20its%20people%2C%20leaving%20behind%20a%20legacy%20of%20trauma.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F209353%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fsophal-ear-1450869%5C%22%3ESophal%20Ear%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Associate%20Professor%20in%20the%20Thunderbird%20School%20of%20Global%20Management%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Farizona-state-university-730%5C%22%3EArizona%20State%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Eunder%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fhenry-kissingers-bombing-campaign-likely-killed-hundreds-of-thousands-of-cambodians-and-set-path-for-the-ravages-of-the-khmer-rouge-209353%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701342010000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30153809%2F52259586497_c299f167c9_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-henry-kissingers-bombing-campaign-killed-thousands-destabilised-cambodia-for-long%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22To%20Kissinger%2C%20Cambodia%20was%20a%20'sideshow'%20during%20the%20Vietnam%20War%2C%20exposing%20the%20story%20of%20America's%20secret%20war%20with%20Cambodia%20from%201969%20to%201973.%20The%20US%20bombing%20of%20ne