iticised%20for%20his%20attitude%20towards%20significant%20war%20crimes%20committed%20by%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Hitchens%2C%20for%20one%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fharpers.org%2Farchive%2F2001%2F02%2Fthe-case-against-henry-kissinger-2%2F%5C%22%3Ecalled%20him%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20war%20criminal%20and%20said%20he%20should%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2016%2Ffeb%2F13%2Fhillary-clinton-henry-kissinger-harms-her-campaign%5C%22%3Etried%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20war%20crimes%2C%20for%20crimes%20against%20humanity%2C%20and%20for%20offenses%20against%20common%20or%20customary%20or%20international%20law%2C%20including%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20murder%2C%20kidnap%2C%20and%20torture%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20impact%20on%20American%20politics%2C%20too%2C%20has%20been%20questioned%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20with%20Thomas%20Meany%20writing%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2020%2F05%2F18%2Fthe-myth-of-henry-kissinger%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20Yorker%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20a%20far%20less%20remarkable%20figure%20that%20his%20supporters%2C%20critics%20and%20he%20himself%20believed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKissinger%2C%20however%2C%20is%20credited%20with%20engaging%20with%20West%20Asia%20to%20end%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%2C%20and%20negotiating%20the%20Paris%20Peace%20Accords%2C%20which%20ended%20American%20involvement%20in%20the%20Vietnam%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20won%20a%20Nobel%20Prize.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Reuters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fhenry-kissinger-american-diplomat-nobel-winner-dead-100-2023-11-30%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20noted%20that%20Kissinger%20had%20been%20active%20with%20meetings%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20leadership%20styles%2C%20and%20testifying%20before%20a%20Senate%20committee%20about%20the%20n